move also means having to commit oneself earlier. Black defences often rely
for their effectiveness on the fact that White must first make a commitment,
and Black can then react appropriately. Once you give the black position an
extra tempo, the boot is on the other foot - in using that extra tempo, he
commits himself, and the black player (playing what is usually the white
position!) can then select a line of play where the extra tempo is less
