{Everyone agrees that the English is characterized by the move 1 c4, but it is
also possible to reach many English lines, by starting out with the move} 1.
Nf3 {. The main advantage of this is that White avoids the whole complex of
lines, starting 1 c4 e5. On the other hand, Black can reply} d5 {, which the
English prevents. I would suggest that the main merit of 1 Nf3 is as an
occasional transpositional trick. When playing an opponent who plays 1...e5
against the English, it is potentially possible to try to move-order him out
of his favourite lines, by starting with the move 1 Nf3, which is something
the English player might like to keep in mind.} *

